The Transport and Freight Forwarding industries are calling for urgent intervention at the Beitbridge border post. Rofhiwa Madzena talks to Lin Botha a representative of the SA Association of Freight Forwarders. #COVID19 #secondwave #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The transport and freight forwarding industries are calling for urgent intervention at the Beitbridge border post. They are arguing that truck drivers are COVID-19 aware but there isn't enough being done to keep them safe at the border. READ: Calls for government intervention at Beitbridge border post The South African Association of Freight Forwarders' Lin Botha said, "the drivers and the transporters are well aware of what happens to them, industry and economic if they aren't truly COVID aware... They are aware of the spread of COVID, that what's makes them nervous when they are bunched up in queues with no sanitation for days and hours." Botha said COVID-19 awareness is being undermined by the conditions at the border posts. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.